  <p>When specifying a color using the HEX system the first two characters are for the red, the second two for the green, and the last are for the blue.  There are lots of color picking tools that you can use that will let you choose the color you want and then tell you the appropriate hex value.</p>
  <subsection xml:id="css_background">
    <title>Background</title>
    <p>CSS has the following properties which we can use to change the background.</p>
    <p>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <p>background-color</p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p>background-image</p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p>background-repeat</p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p>background-attachment</p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p>background-position</p>
        </li>
      </ul>
    </p>
    <listing>
    <program xml:id="css_bkgrd_1" interactive="activecode" language="html" label="program-activecode-css-bkgrd_1" include-source="yes">
      <input>
&lt;html&gt;
   &lt;head&gt;
      &lt;style&gt;
      h1 {
         color: blue;
         font-size: 28pt;
      }
      body {
          background-image: url("http://m.99wallpaper.com/images/7_1306/Black%20Background%20Wood%20-%202560x1600%20by%20Freeman.jpg")
      }
      &lt;/style&gt;
   &lt;/head&gt;
   &lt;body&gt;
      &lt;h1&gt;Hello World!!&lt;/h1&gt;
      &lt;p&gt;The paragraph text should be unchanged&lt;/p&gt;
      &lt;h2&gt;I am not blue!&lt;/h2&gt;
      &lt;h1&gt;Hello Again&lt;/h1&gt;
   &lt;/body&gt;
&lt;/html&gt;
        </input>
      <tests>


</tests>
    </program>
  </listing>
  </subsection>
